  "title": "CHEF",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will lead kitchen operations specializing in Sichuan, Northeastern, and Hunan cuisines, ensuring high-quality food preparation and timely service. You will drive menu planning, staff coordination, and kitchen safety to deliver exceptional dining experiences.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead kitchen operations to maintain excellent food quality and timely service across all shifts</li><li>Plan menus strategically considering budget constraints and seasonal ingredient availability to optimize cost and variety</li><li>Coordinate and support kitchen staff to ensure efficient workflow and adherence to culinary standards</li><li>Train kitchen staff to prepare and cook all menu items consistently and to high standards</li><li>Manage inventory by taking stock of ingredients and equipment, and place timely orders to maintain adequate supplies</li><li>Enforce strict safety and sanitation standards to comply with health regulations and ensure a safe working environment</li><li>Develop innovative recipes to refresh the menu and enhance customer satisfaction</li><li>Monitor industry trends and incorporate relevant innovations to keep the menu competitive and appealing</li><li>Collect and analyze customer and staff feedback to implement continuous improvements in kitchen operations</li><li>Demonstrate flexibility by performing all kitchen roles as needed, including dishwashing and waste disposal</li><li>Commit to working weekends, public holidays, and extended hours to meet operational demands</li></ul>",
